# EED Model Definition

We define computational cost as:

C = αΔS + βE + γD

Where:

- ΔS (Entropy): number of state changes or operations
- E (Energy): execution time (proxy)
- D (Causal Depth): longest dependency chain

## Hypothesis

ΔS, E, and D are structurally coupled.

It may not be possible to construct two algorithms solving the same problem that share identical values across all three dimensions.
